AWKA – The Anambra State police command is investigating the cause of a fire outbreak that gutted a mechanic workshop in Awada, Obosi near Onitsha during which 19 vehicles parked in the workshop were also burnt. The fire, according to eye witness accounts began at about 2am on Friday. The police public relations officer, Mohamed Haruna, said in an interview that though the cause of fire is being investigated, a high tension wire of Enugu Electricity Distribution Company (EEDC) was affected. According to him, it took residents of the area several hours to put off the fire.Nobody was wounded and there was no loss of life either. He said that as soon as the police got wind of the incident, it cordoned the place to prevent hoodlums from having access and looting the place.